The paper deals with the kinematic analysis of a machine tool, which involves the study of the motion of its components. This falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and mechanical engineering (cs.ME). The machine tool is composed of a parallel module and a serial tilting table, which involves the study of systems with multiple degrees of freedom and complex motion, falling under the category of systems and control (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.ROB). Finally, the paper proposes symbolical methods for calculating kinematic solutions, which involves the use of mathematical logic and reasoning, falling under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO).
